<div id="faq" class="wp-block-group"><div class="wp-block-group__inner-container is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained"><section class="container my-14 mx-auto">
			<h2 class="mb-5 text-center title">FAQs</h2>
	
	<div class="w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white shadow-light rounded-2xl">
													<div
					x-data="{open: false}"
					class="flex flex-col py-3 border-b border-gray-200 last:border-0 group hover:bg-transparent"
					itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Question"
				>
					<div class="flex w-full cursor-pointer" @click="open = ! open">
						<div class="flex items-center self-start pr-5 mx-5 border-r border-gray-100 cursor-pointer flex-start h-9">
							<div class="relative flex flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 p-2 transition-all rounded-full group-hover:bg-blue-600">
								<div class="absolute inset-0 w-5 h-5 m-auto">
									<span class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
									<span x-show="!open" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto rotate-90 bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-between w-full gap-4 pr-2 not-prose">
							<p itemprop="name" class="m-0 text-lg font-medium cursor-pointer hover:text-blue-600">
								1. What is Photocase?							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="pt-1 pb-1.5 w-full">
						<div x-show="open" class="mt-4 ml-[101px] text-lg" x-transition itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" x-cloak>
							<div itemprop="text" class="prose">
								<p>Photocase is a&nbsp;new blog dedicated to exploring the world of stock photography and image agencies. It provides tips, insights, and resources for photographers, designers, and creative professionals.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
											<div
					x-data="{open: false}"
					class="flex flex-col py-3 border-b border-gray-200 last:border-0 group hover:bg-transparent"
					itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Question"
				>
					<div class="flex w-full cursor-pointer" @click="open = ! open">
						<div class="flex items-center self-start pr-5 mx-5 border-r border-gray-100 cursor-pointer flex-start h-9">
							<div class="relative flex flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 p-2 transition-all rounded-full group-hover:bg-blue-600">
								<div class="absolute inset-0 w-5 h-5 m-auto">
									<span class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
									<span x-show="!open" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto rotate-90 bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-between w-full gap-4 pr-2 not-prose">
							<p itemprop="name" class="m-0 text-lg font-medium cursor-pointer hover:text-blue-600">
								2. Is Photocase still a&nbsp;stock agency?							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="pt-1 pb-1.5 w-full">
						<div x-show="open" class="mt-4 ml-[101px] text-lg" x-transition itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" x-cloak>
							<div itemprop="text" class="prose">
								<p>No, Photocase is no longer a&nbsp;stock agency. Instead, it has transitioned to being an affiliate partner of Stockphotos.com and Shutterstock.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
											<div
					x-data="{open: false}"
					class="flex flex-col py-3 border-b border-gray-200 last:border-0 group hover:bg-transparent"
					itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Question"
				>
					<div class="flex w-full cursor-pointer" @click="open = ! open">
						<div class="flex items-center self-start pr-5 mx-5 border-r border-gray-100 cursor-pointer flex-start h-9">
							<div class="relative flex flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 p-2 transition-all rounded-full group-hover:bg-blue-600">
								<div class="absolute inset-0 w-5 h-5 m-auto">
									<span class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
									<span x-show="!open" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto rotate-90 bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-between w-full gap-4 pr-2 not-prose">
							<p itemprop="name" class="m-0 text-lg font-medium cursor-pointer hover:text-blue-600">
								3. What kind of content can I find on the Photocase blog?							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="pt-1 pb-1.5 w-full">
						<div x-show="open" class="mt-4 ml-[101px] text-lg" x-transition itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" x-cloak>
							<div itemprop="text" class="prose">
								<p>The Photocase blog covers topics such as stock photography trends, tips for finding the right images, comparisons of stock agencies, and advice for creatives working with visuals.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
											<div
					x-data="{open: false}"
					class="flex flex-col py-3 border-b border-gray-200 last:border-0 group hover:bg-transparent"
					itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Question"
				>
					<div class="flex w-full cursor-pointer" @click="open = ! open">
						<div class="flex items-center self-start pr-5 mx-5 border-r border-gray-100 cursor-pointer flex-start h-9">
							<div class="relative flex flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 p-2 transition-all rounded-full group-hover:bg-blue-600">
								<div class="absolute inset-0 w-5 h-5 m-auto">
									<span class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
									<span x-show="!open" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto rotate-90 bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-between w-full gap-4 pr-2 not-prose">
							<p itemprop="name" class="m-0 text-lg font-medium cursor-pointer hover:text-blue-600">
								4. Can I purchase images directly through Photocase?							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="pt-1 pb-1.5 w-full">
						<div x-show="open" class="mt-4 ml-[101px] text-lg" x-transition itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" x-cloak>
							<div itemprop="text" class="prose">
								<p>No, Photocase does not sell images directly. However, as an affiliate partner, it connects users to Stockphotos.com and Shutterstock, where they can find and purchase high-quality stock photos.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
											<div
					x-data="{open: false}"
					class="flex flex-col py-3 border-b border-gray-200 last:border-0 group hover:bg-transparent"
					itemprop="mainEntity" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Question"
				>
					<div class="flex w-full cursor-pointer" @click="open = ! open">
						<div class="flex items-center self-start pr-5 mx-5 border-r border-gray-100 cursor-pointer flex-start h-9">
							<div class="relative flex flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 p-2 transition-all rounded-full group-hover:bg-blue-600">
								<div class="absolute inset-0 w-5 h-5 m-auto">
									<span class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
									<span x-show="!open" class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-px m-auto rotate-90 bg-blue-600 group-hover:bg-white"></span>
								</div>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="flex items-center justify-between w-full gap-4 pr-2 not-prose">
							<p itemprop="name" class="m-0 text-lg font-medium cursor-pointer hover:text-blue-600">
								5. Who is Photocase for?							</p>
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="pt-1 pb-1.5 w-full">
						<div x-show="open" class="mt-4 ml-[101px] text-lg" x-transition itemscope itemprop="acceptedAnswer" itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" x-cloak>
							<div itemprop="text" class="prose">
								<p>Photocase is designed for anyone interested in stock photography, including photographers, content creators, marketers, and graphic designers looking for insights and resources related to image sourcing.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
						</div>
</section>
